    <section id="faq">
        <div class="left-column">
            <h3>What are gift subscriptions?</h3>

            <p>Gift subscriptions are a way for you to give the gift of The New York Times. A gift subscription at
                the education rate is for one year or four years, and your one-time payment covers the full subscription period.
                If gift recipients choose to extend access beyond the gift subscription period, they will enter their
                own billing information and pay for continued service.</p>

            <p>Choose one of these three packages for your gift subscription:</p>
            <strong>Basic:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Access to NYTimes.com and all NYTimes apps.</li>
                <li>Unlimited article access, anytime, anywhere.</li>
                <li>Discounts to The Times Store, Film Club, Wine Club and TimesTalks.</li>
            </ul>
            <strong>All Access:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Access to exclusive, behind-the-scenes stories, photos and videos from our journalists inside the newsroom.</li>
                <li>Attend live panel discussions and special events hosted by Times editors and journalists.</li>
                <li>Access to a weekly “Inside The Times” podcast series and a collection of 120+ e-books — collections of our most important stories — curated by Times editors.</li>
            </ul>
            <strong>Home Delivery + All Access:</strong>
            <ul style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
                <li>Convenient and reliable delivery. Guaranteed.</li>
                <li>Customized delivery options such as Sunday only, Fri.–Sun., weekday delivery or daily delivery.</li>
                <li>Includes weekly Sunday magazine and monthly T Magazine.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>*Gift subscriptions do not include e-reader editions or digital versions of The New York Times Crossword. Mobile apps are not supported on all devices. Offer not available for current subscribers. Home Delivery offer valid for new subscribers in areas served by The New York Times Delivery Service. All subscriptions will automatically renew and your credit card or PayPal account will be charged in advance of each four-week billing period unless canceled. Other restrictions and taxes may apply.</p>

            <p>Please note, gift subscriptions are for new subscribers only, the recipient cannot have an
                existing digital or home delivery subscription.</p>

            <h3>Can I purchase a gift subscription for someone who is already a subscriber?</h3>

            <p>No. You can only give a gift subscription to a new subscriber. If the intended recipient is an
                existing digital or home delivery subscriber, they won’t be able to redeem the gift.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="right-column">
            <h3>How is the gift subscription delivered?</h3>

            <p>You will be required to supply the recipient's school email address and a delivery date during the
                purchase. An email containing a redemption code is sent to the recipient email address you provide on
                the date you specify. You will also have the option to include a short message that will be in the
                redemption email.</p>

            <h3>Can I purchase multiple gift subscriptions?</h3>

            <p>Yes. After completing a gift purchase, press the Buy Another Gift button. Please note, a single recipient
                cannot redeem multiple gift subscriptions at once.</p>

            <h3>Can I schedule the delivery of my gift?</h3>

            <p>Yes — you can set the date the gift email will be sent to the recipient during the order process. The
                gift email will not be sent until processing is complete. Processing of a gift subscription purchase
                normally takes 24 hours and may take up to 72 hours.</p>

            <h3>What are the terms of sale for gift subscriptions?</h3>

            <p>The full purchase price for gift subscriptions will be charged at the time of purchase and is
                nonrefundable.</p>

            <p>Gift subscriptions are discussed under one-time purchases in the NYTimes Terms of Sale. Redemption codes
                are not replaceable and will expire if not redeemed within five years of the purchase date.</p>

            <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/content/help/account/purchases/subscriptions-and-purchases.html"
               target="_blank">View our complete FAQ section &#187;</a>

        </div>
    </section>


    <section id="legal">
        <sup>*</sup>
        Gift subscriptions can only be purchased for users who are not currently subscribed. Please allow 24 hours for
        gift subscription order processing. Promotional offers for new subscribers only. As part of the order process,
        you must provide the recipient's valid school email address. Smartphone and tablet apps are not supported on all
        devices. Subscriptions do not include e-reader editions, Times Experience content or digital version of The New
        York Times Crossword. Prices shown are in U.S. dollars. Gift subscription period begins the day of redemption.
        Redemption codes expire five years after date of purchase. Other restrictions apply. To learn about all of our
        education rates, please visit <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/subscriptions/edu/lp3HLK4.html?campaignId=3J97Q"
